ASCII Char Set

ASCII stands for American Standard Code for Information Interchange

Represented from one byte, devided into 4 groups of 32 character.
At first group, form a special set of non-printing character called control character.
At second group, comprise various punctuation symbols, special char, and numeric digits.
At third group, reserved for upper case alphabetic char. The remaining codes hold various special symbols.
at fourth group, reserved for lower case alphabetic char. The remaining codes hold special symbols, and one control character(delete).

